        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H|summary=MongoDB is prone to a certificate validation vulnerability.|insight=Under certain configurations of --tlsCAFile and tls.CAFile,
  MongoDB Server may skip peer certificate validation which may result in untrusted connections to
  succeed. This may effectively reduce the security guarantees provided by TLS and open connections
  that should have been closed due to failing certificate validation.

  Required Configuration: A server process will allow incoming connections to skip peer certificate
  validation if the server process was started with TLS enabled (net.tls.mode set to allowTLS,
  preferTLS, or requireTLS) and without a net.tls.CAFile configured.|affected=MongoDB version 3.2.6 through 4.4.28, 5.x through 5.0.24,
  5.1.x through 6.0.13 and 6.1.x through 7.0.5.|impact=|solution=Update to version 4.4.29, 5.0.25, 6.0.14, 7.0.6 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">Update to version 4.4.29, 5.0.25, 6.0.14, 7.0.6 or later.</solution>
        <refs>
